<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>D. Bernaudeau</title><link href="http://didier.bernaudeau.net/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="http://didier.bernaudeau.net/feeds/all.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>http://didier.bernaudeau.net/</id><updated>2015-06-14T22:25:00+02:00</updated><entry><title>Lenovo ThinkPad X240</title><link href="http://didier.bernaudeau.net/Lenovo-ThinkPad-X240.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-06-14T22:25:00+02:00</updated><author><name>Didier Bernaudeau</name></author><id>tag:didier.bernaudeau.net,2015-06-12:Lenovo-ThinkPad-X240.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;This article describes the configuration of my Lenovo ThinkPad X240 (20ALCT01WW) based on Intel Haswell processor. Future articles will refer to this one.&lt;/p&gt;

