</summary><category term="ThinkPad X24O"></category></entry><entry><title>HowTo support FAT64 on Gentoo</title><link href="http://didier.bernaudeau.net/HowTo-support-FAT64-on-Gentoo.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-06-02T18:10:00+02:00</updated><author><name>Didier Bernaudeau</name></author><id>tag:didier.bernaudeau.net,2015-06-02:HowTo-support-FAT64-on-Gentoo.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;FAT64 or ExFAT (Extended File Allocation Table) is a file system introduced in 2009 by Microsoft. This is the successor to FAT32 that addresses the need to store larges files. With FAT64, the theoretical maximum file size is 64 ZB instead of 4GB for FAT32.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This file systen is supported by Microsoft Windows (XP, Vista, Seven,...), MacOS, Linux and Android. For linux, FAT64 is not supported directly in the kernel but with FUSE (Filesystem&amp;nbsp;in UserSpacE).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This article describes step by step how to support FAT64 on Gentoo Linux.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="section" id="installation"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kernel configuration :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code ini literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;     &lt;span class="err"&gt;File&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;systems&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class="err"&gt;---&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;      &lt;span class="err"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;lt;*&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;FUSE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;(Filesystem&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Userspace)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;support&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;      &lt;span class="err"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;lt;*&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class="err"&gt;Character&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;device&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Userspace&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;support&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;software installation :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; emerge sys-fs/fuse-exfat sys-fs/exfat-utils
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="usage"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Format the partition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; mkfs.exfat /dev/sdxy
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the partition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; fsck.exfat /dev/sdxy
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mount the partition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; mount -t exfat /dev/sdxy /mnt/usb
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="references"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;References&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/955704/"&gt;Microsoft - Description of the ExFAT file system driver&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</summary><category term="HowTo"></category><category term="Gentoo"></category></entry><entry><title>HowTo make a web site with Pelican hosted on GitHub Pages</title><link href="http://didier.bernaudeau.net/HowTo-make-a-web-site-with-Pelican-hosted-on-GitHub-Pages.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-05-30T21:58:00+02:00</updated><author><name>Didier Bernaudeau</name></author><id>tag:didier.bernaudeau.net,2015-05-16:HowTo-make-a-web-site-with-Pelican-hosted-on-GitHub-Pages.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Pelican is a static site generator writed in Python. This means that you edit the content on your computer with a simple text editor. Then, a generator makes all HTML pages for the web site, including indexes for articles, categories and tags. In the end, your web site can be hosted easily on a simple HTTP server like GitHub Pages or Amazon S3.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike other CMS (Content Management System) like Wordpress or Drupal, Pelican has no web administration interface. In most cases, the administration interface has many vulnerabilies used to deface the website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This article describes step by step how to make your web site with Pelican 3.5 on Gentoo Linux and how to host your web site on GitHub Pages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="section" id="install-pelican"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Install Pelican&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; emerge pelican
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="create-github-space"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Create GitHub space&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;, create an account named &amp;quot;didier-bernaudeau&amp;quot; then a repository named &amp;quot;didier-bernaudeau.github.io&amp;quot;. Obviously, remplace &amp;quot;didier-bernaudeau&amp;quot; by your username.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="dns-configuration"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;DNS Configuration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add a record in the DNS :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code ini literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;Type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;CNAME&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;Name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;didier.bernaudeau.net&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;Value&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;didier-bernaudeau.github.io.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check configuration with &amp;quot;dig&amp;quot; tool :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;#&lt;/span&gt; emerge &lt;span class="nb"&gt;bind&lt;/span&gt;-tools
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; dig didier.bernaudeau.net +nostats +nocomments +nocmd
&lt;span class="go"&gt;
; &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; DiG 9.10.1-P1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; didier.bernaudeau.net +nostats +nocomments +nocmd
;; global options: +cmd
;didier.bernaudeau.net.         IN      A
didier.bernaudeau.net.  10800   IN      CNAME   didier-bernaudeau.github.io.
didier-bernaudeau.github.io. 3600 IN    CNAME   github.map.fastly.net.
github.map.fastly.net.  30      IN      A       185.31.17.133&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="create-local-directory"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Create local directory&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; git clone https://github.com/didier-bernaudeau/didier-bernaudeau.github.io.git/ MyWebSite
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;MyWebSite
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="create-project"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Create project&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="gp"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; pelican-quickstart
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre class="code ini literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;want&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;your&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;web&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;site?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;[.]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;What&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;will&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;be&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;title&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;web&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;site?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;D.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Bernaudeau&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Who&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;will&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;be&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;author&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;web&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;site?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;D.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Bernaudeau&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;What&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;will&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;be&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;language&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;web&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;site?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;[en]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;want&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;specify&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;URL&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;prefix?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;e.g.,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;http://example.com&lt;/span&gt;   &lt;span class="err"&gt;(Y/n)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Y&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;What&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;your&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;URL&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;prefix?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;(see&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;above&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;; no trailing slash) http://didier.bernaudeau.net&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;Do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;want&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;enable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;article&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;pagination?&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;(Y/n)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;
